Key market players in the global scheduled bus transport industry include established companies such as Greyhound Lines, National Express, FlixBus, Megabus, and Stagecoach Group. These players operate extensive bus networks across multiple regions, offering diverse service types to cater to varying passenger needs. Additionally, companies like Transdev, FirstGroup, and regional entities like Kerala State Road Transport Corporation (KSRTC) and Maharashtra State Road Transport Corporation (MSRTC) contribute significantly to the market's growth by providing reliable and efficient bus services. Furthermore, transportation conglomerates like East Japan Railway Company integrate bus transport as part of their multimodal network, enhancing connectivity and convenience for passengers.

